"second","eliab","third"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_11","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":11,"text":"Masmana the fourth, Jeremias the fifth,","searchKeywords":["masmana","the","fourth","jeremias","fifth"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_12","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":12,"text":"Jethi the sixth, Eliab the seventh,","searchKeywords":["jethi","the","sixth","eliab","seventh"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_13","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":13,"text":"Joanan the eighth, Eleazer the ninth,","searchKeywords":["joanan","the","eighth","eleazer","ninth"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_14","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":14,"text":"Jeremia the tenth, Melchabanai the eleventh.","searchKeywords":["jeremia","the","tenth","melchabanai","eleventh"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_15","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":15,"text":"These chiefs of the army of the sons of Gad, the least one commander of a hundred, and the greatest one of a thousand.","searchKeywords":["these","chiefs","the","army","sons","gad","least","one","commander","hundred","and","greatest","thousand"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_16","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":16,"text":"These the that crossed over Jordan in the first month, and it had overflowed all its banks; and they drove out all the inhabitants of the valleys, from the east to the west.","searchKeywords":["these","the","that","crossed","over","jordan","first","month","and","had","overflowed","all","its","banks","they","drove","out","inhabitants","valleys","from","east","west"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_17","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":17,"text":"And there came of the sons of Benjamin and Juda to the assistance of David.","searchKeywords":["and","there","came","the","sons","benjamin","juda","assistance","david"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_18","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":18,"text":"And David went out to meet them, and said to them, If ye are come peaceably to me, let my heart be at peace with you: but if to betray me to my enemies unfaithfully, the God of your fathers look upon it, and reprove it.","searchKeywords":["and","david","went","out","meet","them","said","are","come","peaceably","let","heart","peace","with","you","but","betray","enemies","unfaithfully","the","god","your","fathers","look","upon","reprove"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_19","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":19,"text":"And the Spirit came upon Amasai, a captain of the thirty, and he said, Go, David, son of Jesse, thou and thy people, peace, peace be to thee, and peace to thy helpers, for thy God has helped thee. And David received them, and made them captains of the forces.","searchKeywords":["and","the","spirit","came","upon","amasai","captain","thirty","said","david","son","jesse","thou","thy","people","peace","thee","helpers","for","god","has","helped","received","them","made","captains","forces"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_20","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":20,"text":"And came to David from Manasse, when the Philistines came against Saul to war: and he helped them not, because the captains of the Philistines took counsel, saying, With the heads of those men will he return to his master Saul.","searchKeywords":["and","came","david","from","manasse","when","the","philistines","against","saul","war","helped","them","not","because","captains","took","counsel","saying","with","heads","those","men","will","return","his","master"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_21","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":21,"text":"When David was going to Sikelag, there came to him of Manasse, Edna and Jozabath, and Rodiel, and Michael, and Josabaith, and Elimuth, and Semathi: are the captains of thousands of Manasse.","searchKeywords":["when","david","was","going","sikelag","there","came","him","manasse","edna","and","jozabath","rodiel","michael","josabaith","elimuth","semathi","are","the","captains","thousands"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_22","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":22,"text":"And they fought on the side of David against a troop, for they all men of might; and they were commanders in the army, of might.","searchKeywords":["and","they","fought","the","side","david","against","troop","for","all","men","might","were","commanders","army"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_23","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":23,"text":"For daily men came to David, to a great force, as the force of God.","searchKeywords":["for","daily","men","came","david","great","force","the","god"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_24","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":24,"text":"And these the names of the commanders of the army, who came to David to Chebron, to turn the kingdom of Saul to him according to the word of the Lord.","searchKeywords":["and","these","the","names","commanders","army","who","came","david","chebron","turn","kingdom","saul","him","according","word","lord"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_25","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":25,"text":"The sons of Juda, bearing shields and spears, six thousand and eight hundred mighty in war.","searchKeywords":["the","sons","juda","bearing","shields","and","spears","six","thousand","eight","hundred","mighty","war"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_26","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":26,"text":"Of the sons of Symeon mighty for battle, seven thousand and a hundred.","searchKeywords":["the","sons","symeon","mighty","for","battle","seven","thousand","and","hundred"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_27","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":27,"text":"Of the sons of Levi, four thousand and six hundred.","searchKeywords":["the","sons","levi","four","thousand","and","six","hundred"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_28","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":28,"text":"And Joadas the chief of Aaron, and with him three thousand and seven hundred.","searchKeywords":["and","joadas","the","chief","aaron","with","him","three","thousand","seven","hundred"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_29","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":29,"text":"And Sadoc, a young mighty in strength, and twenty-two leaders of his father's house.","searchKeywords":["and","sadoc","young","mighty","strength","twenty","two","leaders","his","father","house"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_30","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":30,"text":"And of the sons of Benjamin, the brethren of Saul, three thousand: and still the greater part of them kept the guard of the house of Saul.","searchKeywords":["and","the","sons","benjamin","brethren","saul","three","thousand","still","greater","part","them","kept","guard","house"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_31","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":31,"text":"And of the sons of Ephraim, twenty thousand and eight hundred mighty men, famous in the houses of their fathers.","searchKeywords":["and","the","sons","ephraim","twenty","thousand","eight","hundred","mighty","men","famous","houses","their","fathers"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_32","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":32,"text":"And of the half-tribe of Manasse, eighteen thousand, even who were named by name, to make David king.","searchKeywords":["and","the","half","tribe","manasse","eighteen","thousand","even","who","were","named","name","make","david","king"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_33","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":33,"text":"And of the sons of Issachar having wisdom with regard to the times, knowing what Israel should do, two hundred; and all their brethren with them.","searchKeywords":["and","the","sons","issachar","having","wisdom","with","regard","times","knowing","what","israel","should","two","hundred","all","their","brethren","them"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_34","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":34,"text":"And of Zabulon they that went out to battle, with all weapons of war, fifty thousand to help David, not weak-handed.","searchKeywords":["and","zabulon","they","that","went","out","battle","with","all","weapons","war","fifty","thousand","help","david","not","weak","handed"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_35","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":35,"text":"And of Nephthali a thousand captains, and with them with shields and spears, thirty-seven thousand.","searchKeywords":["and","nephthali","thousand","captains","with","them","shields","spears","thirty","seven"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_36","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":36,"text":"And of the Danites ready for war twenty-eight thousand and eight hundred.","searchKeywords":["and","the","danites","ready","for","war","twenty","eight","thousand","hundred"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_37","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":37,"text":"And of Aser, they that went out to give aid in war, forty thousand.","searchKeywords":["and","aser","they","that","went","out","give","aid","war","forty","thousand"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_38","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":38,"text":"And from the country beyond Jordan, from Ruben, and the Gadites, and from the half-tribe of Manasse, a hundred and twenty thousand, with all weapons of war.","searchKeywords":["and","from","the","country","beyond","jordan","ruben","gadites","half","tribe","manasse","hundred","twenty","thousand","with","all","weapons","war"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_39","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":39,"text":"All these men of war, setting in battle array, with a peaceful mind , and they came to Chebron to make David king over all Israel: and the rest of Israel one mind to make David king.","searchKeywords":["all","these","men","war","setting","battle","array","with","peaceful","mind","and","they","came","chebron","make","david","king","over","israel","the","rest","one"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_40","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":40,"text":"And they were there three days eating and drinking, for their brethren made preparations.","searchKeywords":["and","they","were","there","three","days","eating","drinking","for","their","brethren","made","preparations"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_12_41","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":12,"verse":41,"text":"And their neighbours, as far as Issachar and Zabulon and Nephthali, brought to them upon camels, and asses, and mules, and upon calves, victuals, meal, cakes of figs, raisins, wine, and oil, calves and sheep abundantly: for joy in Israel.","searchKeywords":["and","their","neighbours","far","issachar","zabulon","nephthali","brought","them","upon","camels","asses","mules","calves","victuals","meal","cakes","figs","raisins","wine","oil","sheep","abundantly","for","joy","israel"]}]